The test

  isX.module-writeln.chpl

tests the various isXxx, isXxxType, isXxxValue predicates.
It applies them to module-level variables
and displays the result using writeln().

Other variations on this test could be added, e.g.:
- apply the predicates to local variables,
  formals, directly to types, etc.
- display the results using compilerWarning, e.g.
    result = isXxx(yyy);
    compilerWarning(result:string)
    // or
    if result then compilerWarning("yes");
              else compilerWarning("no");

The test was generated automatically using:

  src/isX.module-writeln.gen

It is added to version control for ease of use.
